{
  "_comment": [
    "Read-differential corpus for the vault read overlay's directory-listing load",
    "(DocMountDocumentsRepository.findManyByMountPointsInFolder). The fixture builder",
    "seeds two pinned document stores (doc_mount_points) and writes a set of files via",
    "v4's real writeDatabaseDocument (QUILLTAP_JOB_CHILD=1 to skip reindex). Both v4 and",
    "the Rust port then READ the SAME fixture .db, so every minted id/timestamp is",
    "identical on both sides — the returned rows compare exactly (no normalization), only",
    "sorted by (mountPointId, relativePath) to neutralize natural row order.",
    "Coverage: matching Prompts/ and Scenarios/ files across two stores (the IN-clause);",
    "decoys that must be excluded — a top-level file (no folder prefix), a nested file",
    "(non-recursive single-level only), and a wrong-extension file; plus an empty",
    "mount-point list (short-circuit to []).",
    "SAFETY: testPepperBase64 is a THROWAWAY 32-byte key, the same one every other tier-2",
    "fixture uses; it decrypts nothing real."
  ],
